I’m using wpilibpi to track balls. I would like to process the image on my Pi and send just the x offset via network tables. The example java application I downloaded from wpilibpi is a camera server that streams the camera over network tables along with the pipeline thread I created.

Is it possible to use the pi as a coprocessor and JUST send the x offset through network tables without sending the camera feed? We already have a driver cam and I’m afraid of hogging up bandwidth with this secondary vision camera. I would appreciate any examples. I’m using Java. Thank you.

Yes this is possible. I have done it with a Pixycam. You still need network tables, but I think the app will work without a cameraserver instance. I am not sure tuning it will work though.

Once tuned, it should work with no camerserver instance. If it does not, you could always host an instamlnce of the server on the pi and use the pins to communicate directly to the Rio.

This should work even of you do not connwct the ethernet port to the radio.
